TransmonDipoleCoupling(
    g_ij::Float64,
    pair::Tuple{Int, Int},
    sub_systems::Vector{QuantumSystem};
    kwargs...
) -> QuantumSystemCoupling Returns a  QuantumSystemCoupling  object for a transmon qubit. In the lab frame, the Hamiltonian coupling term is \[H = g_{ij} (a_i + a_i^\dagger) (a_j + a_j^\dagger)\] In the rotating frame, the Hamiltonian coupling term is \[H = g_{ij} (a_i a_j^\dagger + a_i^\dagger a_j)\] where  a_i  is the annihilation operator for the  i th transmon. source

